PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1782202689
OL,3,CFrom Red Wall revival to party revolt:
OL,4,CHow Keir Starmer's career unfolded
OL,6,FStarmer became Labour leader at the
OL,7,Fheight of the pandemic and led the
OL,8,Fresponse to the flouting of lockdown
OL,9,Frules inside Boris Johnson's
OL,10,Fgovernment.
OL,12,FAfter a campaign centred on change and
OL,13,F"stopping the chaos" of the Tories,
OL,14,FStarmer became prime minister with a
OL,15,Fhuge Labour majority of 411 seats at
OL,16,Fthe 2024 general election.
OL,18,F"Politics can be a force for good and
OL,19,Fthat is how we will govern," he said
OL,20,Fat the time. "Country first, party
OL,21,Fsecond."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
